\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 STEP 3
\f1\b0\fs27 Now make the tomato sauce. Drain some of the juice from the can and tip the rest into a bowl with the olive oil, oregano and a generous pinch of salt, then either scrunch everything together with your fingers for a chunky sauce or blitz with a\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/content/top-five-hand-blenders"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 \strokec4 stick blender}}\'a0if you want it smooth. Tie the basil stalks together, bruise with the back of a knife and place in the sauce. Leave the sauce at room temperature until needed.\cb1 \uc0\u8232 
